citations:
    citation-adwd-prologue:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "Prologue"
            text_from_source: "Abomination, he heard Haggon saying. It was almost as if he were here, in this very room. 'She is just some ugly spearwife,' Varamyr told him. 'I am a great man. I am Varamyr, the warg, the skinchanger, it is not right that she should live and I should die.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Varamyr Sixskins. A dying skinchanger wargs into his wolf One Eye as his second life after attempting and failing to seize Thistle. Establishes the rules of skinchanging: eating human flesh is abomination, seizing a human body is the worst abomination of all. Varamyr's mentor Haggon taught him these laws before Varamyr killed him and took his wolf Greyskin. The prologue also confirms Mance Rayder has been captured by Stannis and the wildling host scattered."
